<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Bspwm on Saitech</title><link>https://saitech.blog/tags/bspwm/</link><description>Recent content in Bspwm on Saitech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 13 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://saitech.blog/tags/bspwm/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>My First Arch Linux Rice Setup</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/my-first-arch-linux-rice-setup/</link><pubDate>Thu, 13 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/my-first-arch-linux-rice-setup/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/my-first-arch-linux-rice-setup/1.png" alt="Featured image of post My First Arch Linux Rice Setup" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;What more to say? 🎉 Today I published my first &lt;code&gt;rice&lt;/code&gt; on Arch Linux for the &lt;code&gt;bspwm&lt;/code&gt; WM. You can find the link &lt;b&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://www.reddit.com/r/unixporn/comments/1j9uzyy/bspwm_white_hole_first_rice/#lightbox" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;. 🎉😄&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hope that adds some extra excitement!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rice is a term used in the Linux community to describe the process of customizing and configuring a Linux setup to suit one&amp;rsquo;s personal preferences. It typically involves adjusting themes, icons, window manager settings, and other system aesthetics to make the environment unique and visually appealing.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description></item><item><title>Arch News Alert</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/arch-news-alert/</link><pubDate>Thu, 20 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/arch-news-alert/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/arch-news-alert/3.png" alt="Featured image of post Arch News Alert" /&gt;&lt;h2 id="why"&gt;Why?
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;I got tired of manually checking &lt;a class="link" href="https://archlinux.org/news" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;archlinux.org/news&lt;/a&gt; every day just to see if there were any critical updates requiring manual steps (you know, the dreaded &lt;code&gt;manual intervention&lt;/code&gt;). So, I decided to automate it by adding a simple notification to my Polybar that shows the latest news headline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When clicked, the notification disappears, and if manual intervention is required, it highlights the alert with exclamation marks—ensuring important updates aren’t missed and the system stays stable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/arch-news-alert/2.png"
width="1493"
height="489"
srcset="https://saitech.blog/p/arch-news-alert/2_hu_ea68053dd90a2daa.png 480w, https://saitech.blog/p/arch-news-alert/2_hu_51c312f7c2e7446b.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="305"
data-flex-basis="732px"
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="module"&gt;Module
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add the following to your module file inside your rice folder:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;[module/arch_news]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;type = custom/script
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;exec = /home/saiphe/.config/bspwm/src/arch_news.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;interval = 10 ; fetch every 10 seconds, adjust as needed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;format-prefix = &amp;#34;&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;format-underline = #5E81AC
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;click-left = ~/.config/bspwm/src/arch_news.sh clear &amp;amp;&amp;amp; xdg-open https://archlinux.org/news/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="config"&gt;Config
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now, include the new module in your Polybar configuration. Add &lt;code&gt;arch_news&lt;/code&gt; to your module list, along with a separator &lt;code&gt;sep&lt;/code&gt; if you prefer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;modules-center = arch_news
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="script"&gt;Script
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Save the following script as &lt;code&gt;arch_news.sh&lt;/code&gt; in your &lt;code&gt;bspwm&lt;/code&gt; script directory &lt;code&gt;~/.config/bspwm/src/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;10
